SIMPLE: nutritive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nutritive
<hw>Nu"tri*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>nutritif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to nutrition; <as>as,
the <ex>nutritive</ex> functions</as>; having the quality of nourishing;
nutritious; nutrimental; alimental; <as>as, <ex>nutritive</ex> food or
berries</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nutritive plasma</b></col>. <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <cd>See
<er>Idioplasma</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Nutritive polyp</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any one of the zooids of a compound hydroid, or
coral, which has a mouth and digestive cavity.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Nu"tri*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Nu"tri*tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nutriture</ent>⟦br⟧
